Discords are fine and harmless, as long as they are only for fans. It only becomes risky and dangerous when these servers are used as vehicles to groom vtubers.
Official or unofficial, it all goes to shit the minute a vtuber joins, because there is no way of knowing what is happening behind the scenes in secret channels or hidden side servers.
WACTOR was in many ways the worse case scenario because you had a small group of fans create a personal server which became the "official" server after the CEO and the vtubers joined. This small group of fans used the server exactly how you would expect any groomer would, to give themselves power and access to the girls, including their YouTube channels.
And they would pressure the girls into using the server for official activities, like meme reviews.

Nisha tried to beat them to the punch by opening an official server herself, but she couldn't handle it and shut it down soon after. She has no plans to remake it, no matter how hard the groomers beg her for it.
